@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - apmconfig/Config
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Config spec, tracked status, and\ndelete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetConfig;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListConfigs using filters apmDomainId,\nconfigType, displayName, optionsGroup;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateConfig when\nno reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteConfig with required\nvia GetConfig or ListConfigs to DELETED\nconfirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetConfig or ListConfigs\nuntil OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields apmDomainId, configType,\nmanagementAgentId,\nmatchAgentsWithAttributeValue;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateConfig only for mutable fields\nagentVersion, attachInstallDir, config,\ndefinedTags (+15 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=read-after-write;\nupdate=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on terminating;
:Keep promotion blocked on drift-guard;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: apmconfig
slug: config
kind: Config
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
follow-up: create=read-after-write;
update=read-after-write; delete=confirm-delete
supported drift: agentVersion, attachInstallDir,
config, definedTags (+15 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
apmDomainId, configType, managementAgentId,
matchAgentsWithAttributeValue
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_apm_config_configs filters
apmDomainId, configType, displayName,
optionsGroup; Pre-create reuse sends apmDomainId
plus configType and any available displayName or
options-group filters, then adopts only a unique
exact match on configType, displayName, group,
filterId, filterText, namespace,
managementAgentId,
matchAgentsWithAttributeValue, and serviceName;
duplicate matches fail instead of guessing.
conflicts: none
open gaps: drift-guard
The published Config kind is polymorphic.
spec.configType selects the OCI subtype decode
path across AGENT, OPTIONS, MACS_APM_EXTENSION,
METRIC_GROUP, APDEX, and SPAN_FILTER, and the
runtime rejects top-level fields that do not
belong to the selected subtype before OCI calls.
The reviewed runtime is synchronous. Create and
update settle from the follow-up read, the row
publishes no provisioning or updating lifecycle
buckets, and delete keeps the finalizer until
confirm-delete rereads stop finding the
resource.
status.apmDomainId mirrors the bound request
domain because OCI response bodies do not echo
it, but replacement-only domain drift still
needs an explicit read model.
APDEX rule booleans remain a current gap in the
generated spec projection. Explicit false values
inside spec.rules[] are not preserved today, so
the handwritten runtime cannot distinguish
omission from false for rules.isEnabled and
rules.isApplyToErrorSpans.
end note
@enduml
